◻ Implemented using Hashmap in C++
◻ Each element has a key-value pair
◻ No two mapped values can have the same key values

Types:
▫ Ordered map
▫ Unordered map

// declaring an ordered map

map<int, int> m1;

// declaring an unordered map
unordered_map<string, int> m2;


◻ Functions on Hashmap

methods               description
insert({k,v})        inserts elements(k,v pair) in the map
find(k)              returns the iterator to the element with key k if found, else returns the  iterator to the end
begin()              returns an iterator to the first element in the map
end()                returns an iterator to the theoretical element that follows the last element in the map
size()               returns the number of elements in the map
empty()              returns true if the map is empty


